The paper proposes a novel matrix completion algorithm for recommendation systems, which is a common problem in machine learning and information retrieval. The algorithm uses techniques from information theory and collaborative filtering, which are typically studied in the sub-categories of cs.IT and cs.IR. The paper also mentions that the algorithm is scalable and performs well on both synthetic and real-world datasets, which are common concerns in the sub-categories of cs.DS and cs.LG.
